Since the city was shut down, many people have taken risks to record the facts and truth of what happened in the city under the epidemic, and the delivery man Zhang Sai is one of them. As a reporter, Zhang also wondered if the words would be like a pebble dropped into the water, with little ripple effect. In fact, the point of these records is not so much that the ripples are short, as that they make other people realize that we can throw chunks out of our chests and get to the bottom of things.

Throw a stone into the water

February 3,2020

The workstations are back. The morning show, the evening show. Everybody chant, everybody make a video. 46 employees, 32. Management said, can come all here, our site is normal.

Management says we're a team. At this very moment, let us fight for victory.

Recall the old novel on a sentence: The best of all, the gods return.

We love being together so much. Meals are served, baths are bathed, and blind dates are set up for free trade.

At the party, everyone was given a case of oranges. Everybody hold the oranges above their heads and shout.

I'm tired of lifting oranges, I said to myself.

I left a few oranges, and half a case for my brother's house. I'll call him and tell him to put his mask on and come down. Sat on the scooter waiting for him to come down, waiting for two minutes did not come down. A little anxious, subconsciously touched the phone. If it's a client, I'll make a call. For takeout, time is money. I put the orange on the ground, I put the Hot Taro on the scooter pedal. Turn around and go your separate ways.

He said he was gonNA come by and get some flour and salt. I said you do not come over, yesterday I had a little cough, today fine, fine also do not come over. Go to the supermarket and buy a pack.

It was getting a little dark at the end of the day. There's a car. Nobody honks. Someone. No one's talking. There's rain. There's rain.

I've been doing takeout in Wuhan for almost a year. Even if I had traversed every road in the vicinity of three kilometers, even if I had seen all the sci fi movies and horror movies, even if I had read all the novels in the world, I could not build in my heart the silence on the streets of Wuhan today.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wuhan, medical workers are disinfection work. Photograph: AP

The outbreak shut a lot of people up. It doesn't matter to me. I don't like to talk. There was a time when I spoke like a poet. Of course, this poem is not the Song of everlasting sorrow.

Why is the world full of lies and nonsense? Why do so many people maintain a world of lies and nonsense?

For a long time, I didn't want to talk. I write articles, I write novels, I write Fairy Tales, I write poems, but I don't contribute. Because the cast also missed, but also because the role of the cast is not as large as a stone thrown into the water ripples.

The outbreak shut people up. To silence the unfortunate around you. I want to talk.

A fool who can't find his way home on a rainy day

February 6,2020

Day 15 of the siege. The smiles are back. Site orders, volume and price increases. Single King came back, we began to gather to ask: Just ran a few single? Eight? You don't leave the house without eight. Take a break. For World Peace. The single king complains, I receive the single is difficult miscellaneous disease.

I haven't laughed or cried in 15 days. I don't take away the right to criticize others for living a happy life. No one has the right. I just find it jarring.

Waiting in line for the harvest. They gathered around the work station to chat. I sat on the electric car in front of my work station and got caught in the rain. Like a fool who doesn't know when to run home in the rain. When I was 27, my dad set me up on my first blind date. He said, "don't be picky, as long as it rains and you run home. ".

The manager came over.

Chang Sai, what's the matter with you? Did you have a fight with your wife?

There's nothing going on.

What's the matter? You look sick.

No, it's not.

What? Your incubation period is over.

It's not my incubation period. It's the incubation period of the people around me.

What are you afraid of? Old People are dying. You don't pay your mortgage?

People are dying all around us! I shouted at him in my mind.

Why do I always want to scare people? Didn't you sing and dance when you took a break yesterday? You think you're GonNa win the lottery, you're GonNa win the Little Guy, and you're not gonna be comfortable with this little dream? Don't bother him. I don't deserve it.

I am now in complete agreement with the book I read on January 15th. The rest of our lives, our happiness, depends on people like my colleagues. The optimistic, the healthy, the kind, the industrious majority. My parents, my brother. Not like me, thinking this and thinking that, walking on the edge of a nervous breakdown. I criticize dad like a Qing Dynasty person. I want to scold him when I think back to the years when he set me up on a blind date. Just because I didn't say it doesn't mean I don't love him. It's common sense.

In memory of Dr Li Wenliang

February 7,2020

I called a client in the 106th. I repeated what I had said a hundred times before: Hello. I'm a delivery guy. I'm already downstairs. I left my stuff downstairs because of the outbreak. Please come down and help yourself. She's in a bit of a pickle. Can't she come up? Can't she come up. Listening to her tone, I would like to say a can like Dr. Li Wenliang. But I know that Dr. Wen-liang Li is also saying in his heart that he can't. I don't have a mask, she said. I was silent for a second or two. Keep telling her what I said: I'm sorry, I can't help it, it's a very difficult time, understand each other. I'm responsible for myself first. Please place your order at your convenience and I will help you with your refund. She said yes. I'm sorry, but I don't think I did anything wrong. I don't want to see morality trump common sense. I think when Dr. Li wrote the word understand, what he understood was how dangerous the virus is. And a lot of people have since learned that. Who Admonished Dr. Lee for doing his job. Justice trumps common sense.

People went to Wuhan Central Hospital to pay their respects to Dr Li Wenliang. Photograph: AP

Today, the name of Li Wenliang spread all over the motherland of the Earth's circle of friends.

Since the essay, we have received a large number of submissions, writing truthfully about what they saw and heard during the epidemic. It will be a sincere and weighty record, and we will keep it.
